@base_url = http://localhost:8000/api

### 1. Demander un OTP (Mauritanie)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/request-otp/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678"}

###

### 2. Demander un OTP (France — membre à l'étranger)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/request-otp/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+33612345678"}

###

### 3. Vérifier l'OTP (remplace 123456 par le code affiché dans la console)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/verify-otp/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678", "code": "602840"}

###

### 4. Créer le PIN
POST {{base_url}}/auth/set-pin/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678", "pin": "1234", "pin_confirm": "1234"}

###

### 5. Connexion
POST {{base_url}}/auth/login/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22200000000", "pin": "0000"}

###

### 6. Réinitialiser PIN — étape 1 (envoie un nouvel OTP)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/reset-pin/request/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678"}

###

### 7. Réinitialiser PIN — étape 2 (confirme OTP + nouveau PIN)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/reset-pin/confirm/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678", "code": "123456", "pin": "5678", "pin_confirm": "5678"}

###

### 8. Test numéro invalide — sans indicatif (doit retourner 400)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/request-otp/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "12345678"}

###

### 9. Test PIN non numérique (doit retourner 400)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/set-pin/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678", "pin": "abcd", "pin_confirm": "abcd"}

###

### 10. Test PIN non concordants (doit retourner 400)
POST {{base_url}}/auth/set-pin/
Content-Type: application/json

{"phone": "+22212345678", "pin": "1234", "pin_confirm": "5678"}

###

